- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is likely because the paper deals with timed extensions of pushdown automata.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is likely because the paper discusses the expressive power and complexity of different models of pushdown automata.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is possible because the paper deals with the stack data structure used in pushdown automata.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is possible because the paper discusses the complexity of the non-emptiness problem for a subclass of pushdown automata.
